                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why the iPhone Air Is the Most Important iPhone You’ll Never Buy]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-the-iphone-air-is-the-most-important-iphone-youll-never-buy/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-air-partial-x-ray-shot.jpg" length="2338" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone Air]]></category><category><![CDATA[battery]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I'm not buying it, either.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I don’t want an iPhone Air, I’m buying the iPhone 17 Pro instead. The Air’s drawbacks just aren’t worth it to me; I don’t want an ultra-thin body at the cost of battery life and camera.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 18:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-the-iphone-air-is-the-most-important-iphone-youll-never-buy/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy One UI 8 Update Release Schedule Revealed]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/samsung-reveals-when-your-galaxy-will-get-android-16/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/a-stylized-layout-featuring-the-android-16-logo-one-ui-8-in-the-center-and-several-samsung-phones-side-by-side.png" length="2010" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Here's when your phone or tablet should get Android 16. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Now that Samsung has finally started officially <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/samsung-galaxy-one-ui-8-android-16-update-officially-begins/" target="_blank">rolling out the big One UI 8 update</a> (based on Android 16) for the Galaxy S25 series, we're learning more about when other devices will get it. Yesterday, Samsung confirmed the launch, and now we have a full release schedule for dozens of devices.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 17:49:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/samsung-reveals-when-your-galaxy-will-get-android-16/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[8 Games That Are Perfect for Social Butterflies]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/games-that-are-perfect-for-social-butterflies/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Timothy Jacob Hudson]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/sharedimages/2024/11/deep-rock-galactic-rogue-core-2.jpg" length="540" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[video games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Helldivers 2]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deep Rock Galactic]]></category><category><![CDATA[RuneScape]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Looking to make some new online friends? These social games are the perfect way to meet new people.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Making friends in an online world can be tough. But thankfully, there are some video games that are perfect for making friends and having a blast. If you love hanging out and using your voice when gaming, these eight titles are perfect for you.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/games-that-are-perfect-for-social-butterflies/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[4 Apple TV+ Premieres Heating Up the Back Half of September]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-tv-premieres-still-to-come-september/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Keeley Brooks]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mixcollage-15-sep-2025-03-59-pm-7510.jpg" length="708" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple TV+]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Apple TV+ wants all your attention for the rest of September.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://shop-links.co/link/?exclusive=1&publisher_slug=howtogeek&u1=UUhtgUeUpU2016588&article_name=4+Apple+TV%2B+Premieres+Heating+Up+the+Back+Half+of+September&article_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fapple-tv-premieres-still-to-come-september%2F&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftv.apple.com%2F" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Apple TV+</a> is continually adding to its library of compelling drama series, which has seen multiple hit releases this year, including <em>Your Friends and Neighbors</em>, <em>Dope Thief</em>, Chief of War, <em>Smoke,</em> and the recently crowned most-winning comedy in Emmy history for a single season, <em>The Studio.</em></p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 16:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-tv-premieres-still-to-come-september/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Search Is Getting a Windows App]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-made-a-desktop-app-for-windows/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/google-search-bar-app-over-windows-desktop.jpg" length="50" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 10]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A search bar on your desktop.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Google is launching a new experimental Google app for Windows in its Labs program, which is designed to help you find what you need much faster. The app lets you search for information without having to switch windows or interrupt what you’re doing, but you have to enable it first.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 16:03:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-made-a-desktop-app-for-windows/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This New EV Just Unlocked the Future of Battery Tech]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/new-ev-just-unlocked-future-battery-tech/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tyler Dupont]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mg4_5-1.jpg" length="174" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Electric Vehicles]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sedans]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A newly revealed EV showcases next-gen batteries with faster charging and longer range, redefining the future of electric cars.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Electric vehicles have long been limited by the trade-offs between range, charging speed, and cost, but a new breakthrough is rewriting the rulebook. A recently launched EV is the first to hit the road with a semi-solid-state battery, a technology that bridges the gap between today’s lithium-ion packs and the long-promised fully solid-state cells.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/new-ev-just-unlocked-future-battery-tech/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[2 New tvOS 26 Features You Won't Get Unless You Upgrade Your Apple TV]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/new-apple-tv-features-you-wont-get-unless-you-upgrade/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Christian Zibreg]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apple-tv-with-the-tvos-26-logo-highlighting-the-liquid-glass-interface-and-karaoke-features.png" length="500" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple TV 4K]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple TV+]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Music]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            These Apple TV features await your upgrade.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>tvOS 26, the renamed Apple TV operating system, introduces two standout features that require the latest hardware. Let's break down what they are, which devices support them, and whether it’s worth upgrading your Apple TV for these new features alone.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 15:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/new-apple-tv-features-you-wont-get-unless-you-upgrade/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[You Can Now Try the Fedora 43 Beta]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/fedora-43-beta-released/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fedora-linux-43-beta-with-the-gnome-desktop-on-a-laptop-screen.jpg" length="288" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Fedora]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><category><![CDATA[gnome]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There's an upgrade to GNOME and to certain Fedora Spin installation experiences.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Fedora Linux team announced today the release of the beta testing version of Fedora 43. This update to the community fork of Red Hat Enterprise Linux brings several changes, which you can test out by installing the beta image.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 15:26:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/fedora-43-beta-released/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Java 25 LTS Is Here, and IntelliJ IDEA Is Ready for It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/java-25-lts-is-here-and-intellij-idea-is-ready-for-it/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/intellij-logo.png" length="670" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Programming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Java 25 is coming with some bad news for 32-bit PCs.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Java 25 LTS is officially here, and with it comes a massive update to IntelliJ IDEA. The new version is all about making the language more accessible for new users and more powerful for experienced developers, with big changes to how you write and run code.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2025 15:21:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/java-25-lts-is-here-and-intellij-idea-is-ready-for-it/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Giant 100-inch Hisense TV Is Over $1,000 Off Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/save-1100-on-this-100-inch-hisense-tv/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/a-100-inch-hisense-tv-on-the-wall-of-a-huge-house.jpg" length="241" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><description><![CDATA[
